<text id="02-output-contract" title="Rails 7+ Backend Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the Rails-app manifest this methodology produces. Validator enforces required keys + per-field constraints.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/ruby-rails.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["rails_version", "ruby_version", "service_result_class_count", "services", "sidekiq_jobs"],
  "properties": {
    "rails_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^(7|8)\\."},
    "ruby_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^3\\."},
    "service_result_class_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1, "maximum": 1},
    "services": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "returns_service_result", "accepts_params_kwarg"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string", "pattern": "Service$"},
          "returns_service_result": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
          "accepts_params_kwarg": {"type": "boolean", "const": true}
        }
      }
    },
    "sidekiq_jobs": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "args_are_primitives", "retry"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string", "pattern": "Job$"},
          "args_are_primitives": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
          "retry": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}
        }
      }
    },
    "forbidden_patterns_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "rails_version": "7.1",
  "ruby_version": "3.3",
  "service_result_class_count": 1,
  "services": [{"class": "Users::CreateService", "returns_service_result": true, "accepts_params_kwarg": true}],
  "sidekiq_jobs": [{"class": "Users::SendWelcomeJob", "args_are_primitives": true, "retry": 5}],
  "forbidden_patterns_found": []
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "rails_version": "5.2",
  "ruby_version": "2.7",
  "service_result_class_count": 4,
  "services": [{"class": "UserManager", "returns_service_result": false, "accepts_params_kwarg": false}],
  "sidekiq_jobs": [{"class": "SendWelcome", "args_are_primitives": false, "retry": 0}],
  "forbidden_patterns_found": ["UserMailer.deliver_later inside ActiveRecord::Base.transaction"]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Rails/Ruby too old; multiple ServiceResult classes; service named UserManager; AR object in Sidekiq args; deliver_later inside transaction.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>`deliver_later` / external HTTP / `Search::Index.update` inside `ActiveRecord::Base.transaction`.</item>
      <item>More than one `class ServiceResult` definition in the repo.</item>
      <item>ActiveRecord object passed as Sidekiq job arg.</item>
      <item>Service calling `params.require(...)` directly (HTTP coupling).</item>
      <item>`remove_column` / `rename_column` migration applied without human approval log.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-ruby-rails.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
